RACE.RACE_TEXT: FERNDALE RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 92. Claiming Purse 9500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIR LAUGHALOT pushed along to the front early, set all the pace from the rail, was clear into the stretch and held under steady urging. HAY JUAN had no speed, saved ground, moved up to second place then outbattled MIKE OPERATOR to the line. MIKE OPERATOR drifted out on the first turn, chased to the second turn, was outkicked by the winner then got outdueleld for second. LIVE A GOOD LIFE was fanned four wide by MIKE OPERATOR to the backstretch, stalked the winner to the second turn then was outkicked to the stretch and did not rally.

ENTRY.NAME: Hay Juan
ENTRY.OWNER: MJ Ranch Ochoa Juan and Orta J Roque
ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, saved ground, dueled for 2d, determined

ENTRY.NAME: Mike Operator
ENTRY.COMMENT: drifted out 1st turn, chased, outkicked, outdueled for 2d

ENTRY.NAME: Live a Good Life
ENTRY.COMMENT: fanned 4 wide 1st turn, stalked pace, outkicked, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Sir Laughalot
ENTRY.COMMENT: pushed for speed, pace rail, clear, held driving

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Dr. & Mrs. William T. Gray DVM

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FERNDALE RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SEIGE THE DAY had good speed, contested the pace inside of BIG BAD BRIAN, responded on the second turn to edge clear into the stretch then held off SMOKIN KEN late. SMOKIN KEN The latter had no speed and trailed while racing off the rail to the second turn, lugged out five deep into the stretch then closed steadily but was too late. ZHIVAGO eased in early, tracked the leaders from the rail to the stretch but could not offer the needed late response. BIG BAD BRIAN attended the pace outside the winner and two wide to the second turn, got outkicked to the stretch then weakened. MISSY PARKER chased the pace two wide for three furlongs, remained two wide to the stretch but tired in the drive.

ENTRY.OWNER: Beckner Teri L and Gallus Bjorn M
ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, trailed, lugged 5wide 2d turn, steady late rally

ENTRY.NAME: Seige the Day
ENTRY.COMMENT: contested pace, responded stretch, clear, held on

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased pace, 2wide, tired stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Big Bad Brian
ENTRY.COMMENT: attended pace, off rail, outkicked, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Zhivago
ENTRY.COMMENT: eased in early, tracked pace rail, asked 2d turn, even late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FERNDALE RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 9000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility And Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHOCKAZULU was chasing after shifting out early, advanced widest on the backstretch, dueled into the second turn while three wide, battled the runnerup to mid stretch then edged away under steady pressure. OBVIOUS hopped in the air at the start and lost about five lengths, chased once settled off the rail, advanced on the backstretch to engage the leaders, dueled the winner into the stretch then was outkicked to the line. HOLYJAZZ had early speed, stayed on to the second turn then was outkicked to the stretch and finished evenly. DAD BOD was fractious in the gate then stalked the pace from the rail to the second turn, remained inside to the stretch but lacked a closing bid. PHANTOMS BOOK hustled and set a pressured pace early, was overtaken on the second turn then came up empty in the drive.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAWK HILL was on the pace to the backstretch, edged away on the second turn, kicked clear to mid stretch then was under steady pressure to hold. STANLEY RYDER had no speed and saved ground to no avail. CABALLERANGO hesitated in the gate, came out awkwardly then was rank in the early stages and trailed.
